@prettynerdy use VLC player. Adjust audio on the fly with J and K buttons while movie is playing. Negative numbers will speed up the audio if it is behind, and positive numbers will sync it if the sound is happening first, then the action. I did not view  this print, but have used this methodology in the past. Generally speaking, if the audio is about a second behind the action, then -200 to -400 seems to do the trick. 60 seconds ahead seems a little much, given there are 4 pages of comments and yours is t he first with this issue. Might I suggest a new codec pack, from somewhere like cnet (download dot com, just google it) - I got my codec pack there and between that and vlc, never have a problem I can't solve on my own, beit sound, gamma lighting in dark places (which this film has many of), etc. Again, have not seen this print, but this does work. That's why so many of us recommend VLC. Cheers
